      "full_body_preview": "The carpenter at the south end of the Barn kept a tally on the back of the door. Not of the boards she cut, but of how many other carpenters borrowed her cuts to true up their own.\n\nFor the first month she came in early to log her finished work in the deliverables ledger. Sixteen frames. Twenty-two frames. Thirty-four frames. The ledger filled with her name. The door stayed empty.\n\nA young carpenter named Po took to leaving a slightly-too-short batten by the saw bench. Not finished, not anything"
